Module clinic
Package clinic

Class ClinicManagerController

java.lang.Object
clinic.ClinicManagerController
public class ClinicManagerController extends Object
ClinicManagerController is responsible for managing clinic operations, including handling appointments, providers, technicians, and patient medical records. It allows for loading provider data, managing the clinic's schedule, and other functionalities. It uses a GUI from JavaFX allowing for specific user input.
Author:
Pranav Sudheer and Pranav Komarla

    • initialize

      public void initialize()
      Initializes the controller class. This method is called after all

    • initializeImageTypes

      private void initializeImageTypes()
      Initializes the available imaging types by adding them to the imagingType combo box.

    • initializeListOrders

      private void initializeListOrders()
      Initializes the list of sorting options for displaying orders in the `orderTypes` ComboBox. Adds three ordering types: "date/time/provider", "patient/date/time", and "county/date/time".

    • sortingType

      private String sortingType()
      Determines the sorting type based on the selected order type from the `orderTypes` ComboBox.
      Returns:
      a string code representing the sorting type: "PA" for "date/time/provider", "PP" for "patient/date/time", "PL" for "county/date/time", or null if no selection is made.

    • displayAppointments

      private void displayAppointments()
      Displays appointments sorted by the selected order type. Retrieves the sorting type using `sortingType()` and checks if there is a valid list of appointments to display. If valid, it calls `printList(sortType)` to output the sorted list; otherwise, displays an error message if the sorting type is missing.

    • displayImagingAppts

      private void displayImagingAppts()
      Displays imaging appointments. Uses the sort type "PI" specifically for imaging appointments, checks the list of appointments, and calls `printList(sortType)` to display them if valid.

    • displayOfficeAppts

      private void displayOfficeAppts()
      Displays office appointments. Uses the sort type "PO" specifically for office appointments, checks the list of appointments, and calls `printList(sortType)` to display them if valid.

    • displayBillingStatements

      private void displayBillingStatements()
      Displays billing statements. Uses the sort type "PS" specifically for billing statements, checks if a valid list exists, and calls `printList(sortType)` to display the statements if valid.

    • displayCreditStatements

      private void displayCreditStatements()
      Displays credit statements. Uses the sort type "PC" specifically for credit statements, checks if a valid list exists, and calls `printList(sortType)` to display the statements if valid.

    • initializeTimeslot

      private void initializeTimeslot(javafx.scene.control.ComboBox<String> timeslot)

      Parameters:
      timeslot - the ComboBox to be populated with time slot options

    • times

      private String times(javafx.scene.control.ComboBox<String> timeSlot)
      Converts the selected time slot in the ComboBox to an integer representation for further processing. Each time corresponds to a specific integer value.
      Parameters:
      timeSlot - the ComboBox containing time slot options
      Returns:
      a string representing the corresponding integer value for the selected time, or null if the time does not match

    • providerId

      private String providerId()
      Retrieves the NPI (National Provider Identifier) of a selected provider from the ComboBox. The provider's name is extracted, and a search is performed in the list of providers to find the corresponding NPI.
      Returns:
      the NPI of the selected provider, or null if not found

    • clearOutput

    • onLoadProvidersButtonClick

    • setAppointment

      private void setAppointment()
      Sets an appointment based on the provided command words. If the command indicates a doctor or technician appointment, it checks for availability and books the appointment accordingly.

    • cancelAppointment

      private void cancelAppointment(String[] command)
      Cancels an appointment if it exists in the list of appointments. Displays a message in the text area indicating whether the appointment was successfully canceled or if it does not exist.
      Parameters:
      command - an array of strings representing the command details

    • rescheduleAppt

      private void rescheduleAppt()
      Reschedules an appointment by creating a new appointment command and calling the reschedule method if the arguments are valid.

    • createRescheduleAppt

      private void createRescheduleAppt()
      Creates the command for rescheduling an appointment based on user input in the corresponding fields. Validates the input fields to ensure dates and required fields are properly filled before creating the command string.

    • reschedule

      private void reschedule(String[] details)
      Reschedules an appointment based on the provided details. Checks if the appointment exists, verifies the new timeslot availability, and updates the appointment details accordingly. Displays relevant messages in the text area based on the operation outcome.
      Parameters:
      details - an array of strings containing details of the appointment to be rescheduled

    • CheckAvailability

      private boolean CheckAvailability(String identifier, String DorT, String timeslot, Date date)
      Checks the availability of a provider for a specific timeslot on a given date. Returns false if the provider is already booked for that timeslot and true otherwise.
      Parameters:
      identifier - the NPI of the provider to check availability
      DorT - indicates if the provider is a doctor or technician
      timeslot - the timeslot to check for conflicts
      date - the date for which availability is being checked
      Returns:
      true if the provider is available for the specified timeslot and date, false if they are not

    • CreateAppointment

      private void CreateAppointment()
      Creates an appointment by collecting details from the input fields. Validates the input to ensure all fields are filled and contain valid data. Builds a command string to represent the appointment details.
